title: Are You Concerned About the Republican Party’s Future?
title_page: Are You Concerned About the Republican Party’s Future? - The New York Times
maintext:
There is deep concern among Republicans about political divisions and the future of the party, according to a new poll from The New York Times and CBS News. Despite his dominance in the primaries and support from voters, some party leaders remain wary of Donald J. Trump’s candidacy for president, even as he approaches the convention in July as the presumptive nominee.
We’d like to hear from the party’s longtime members or those who have just registered as Republicans. How do you see the state of the party and its future? A Times journalist may follow up with you to learn more about your story. Your contact information will not be published.
